# Keep the build context to just the source the Dockerfile COPYs. Without this, `docker build .`
# tars the whole checkout to the daemon — including the live pb_data (DB + AES-encrypted keys), the
# local pocketbase binary, and .env (APP_ENCRYPTION_KEY) — which is slow and a standing footgun if a
# COPY is ever broadened.
.git
.github
pb_data/
pocketbase
*.zip
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
scripts/build-seed/
mobile/
*.md
# self-host (server/) build artifacts + deps — the Dockerfile rebuilds them
node_modules
server/node_modules
server/dist
server/web
core/node_modules
